# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# math-research-pipelines — root .gitignore
#
# These pipelines run entirely from committed source; everything ignored here
# is a *generated* artifact (caches, build output, rendered PDFs). Running the
# test suites repeatedly is therefore tree-clean.
#
# NOTE: lambda2c-emissiongap-verification/output/results.json is intentionally
# TRACKED — it ships as a mostly-empty template and is repopulated on each run
# (see that package's README §6). It is *not* ignored here; reset it with
# `git checkout -- lambda2c-emissiongap-verification/output/results.json`
# rather than committing a locally-populated copy.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Python bytecode / caches ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.hypothesis/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Packaging / build output ---
*.egg-info/
*.egg
build/
dist/
.build/            # matrix-plates `make export` target
pip-wheel-metadata/

# --- Virtual environments ---
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# --- Coverage ---
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
coverage.xml

# --- Generated papers (rendered by build_pdfs.py / LaTeX) ---
lambda2c-emissiongap-verification/output/*.pdf
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.toc

# --- Editor / OS noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.idea/
